You don’t have to wait until Broadway reopens to get a taste of what’s playing.
“Six”Divorced, beheaded, died; divorced, beheaded, survived.
In this buzzy new British import, Henry VIII’s six wives compete to see who got the worst of him.
“The Book of Mormon”The duo behind “South Park” created this irreverent, profanity laced but ultimately warm-hearted musical about clueless missionaries in Africa.
Try “Monty Python’s The Life of Brian,” about the poor sucker who happened to be born one stable away from Jesus Christ.